‚Üê You should ALWAYS composite at the risk of degrading your whole image if you don't. BUT sometimes you don't care and the image blends better without it, so here it's the option.

Select the Wildcard to add to the text

Here it calculates the lowest divisible by 8 resolution and crops the image, taking the extra pixels out. This method instead of resizing is better because the image won't lose any quality, as resizing even by a pixel can damage the original quality. The image will be composited back to the original res at the end of the workflow. (Inpainting ONLY)

This group is to make sure the image is divisible by 8. The ksampler don't deal with images that are not and will change the resolution. The composite in the end would look mismatched without this.

WARNING:If you are painting the borders, this might give you a border pixel on the right or on the bottom, back from the original image. If you don't want that, you can bypass this group so your final image is a new image with a new resolution that IS divisiable by 8.


IF outpainting is ON this will always be OFF because outpainting will always give you new resolution image that is devisable by 8 and it makes no sense to composite back to the original resolution.
